Eskom has announced that it will continue with stage 4 load-shedding this coming week. The company said citizens must prepare for the following power cuts: It added that South Africans can expect “up to stage 4 load-shedding” on Tuesday, too. The power cuts are due to a shortage of capacity, and Eskom said it was working to bring units back online. It stated that stage 4 load-shedding is “no cause for alarm”, however, as “approximately 80%” of the country’s electricity demand is being met.